-- Romanian Utility Seeks Bids for Water Network Upgrades
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2013-09-03T15:30:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-03/romanian-utility-seeks-bids-for-water-network-upgrades.html
Apa Canal 2000 SA, a Romanian
regional utility, is seeking bids for water and sewage upgrades
in the southern county of Arges in contracts valued at 68.1
million lei ($20 million).  The utility is awaiting bids for a 34.5 million-lei
contract to improve and expand the water infrastructure in the
towns of Bascov and Merisani until Oct. 23, according to a
 procurement notice  on the Romanian public auction website.  Bids for a 33.6 million-lei contract to upgrade the water
and sewage network in Topoloveni can also be filed by Oct. 23,
according to a separate notice on the website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
